    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-17T21:18:40+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-17T21:18:40+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T11:48:40Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-17T11:48:40Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system south of the Bight extends a ridge over SA. The high will slowly move east over the weekend ahead of a cold front which will slip to the south of SA and weaken. The high will remain near stationary in the southern Tasman Sea, maintaining a ridge across the state early next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW015" description="Mount Lofty Ranges" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-17T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-17T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Clear. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds easterly 15 to 20 km/h turning north to northeasterly during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:50am to 2:30pm, UV Index predicted to reach 5 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the morning. The chance of a thunderstorm in the morning. Winds north to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h turning westerly in the middle of the day then tending southeast to southwesterly in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 14 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-20T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-21T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-19T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-20T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower about the southern Fleurieu Peninsula in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h turning easterly during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 12 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 22.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-21T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-22T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-20T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-21T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Winds north to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending north to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the day then tending north to northeasterly during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 11 with daytime temperatures reaching the mid to high 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
